        <h1>Filter Row</h1>
        <p>You can use the Filter row to narrow down the list and look for a specific record in the table.</p>
        <p><b>Numeric and Date Search</b>
        </p>
        <p>For Numeric and Date fields, for example: Batch ID, MW, Created, Modified, etc..., following options are available.</p>
        <p>Click on the reset icon in the numeric cells within the filter row, the following options appear:</p>
        <p>
            <img src="../Resources/Images/Web Registration images/numeric search options.gif" />
        </p>
        <p>Use one of the available operators and enter the query value, the records with matching values display.</p>
        <p style="font-weight: bold;">Text Search</p>
        <p>For Text fields, for example: MF, following options are available:</p>
        <p>
            <img src="../Resources/Images/Web Registration images/text field.gif" />
        </p>
        <p>The following screen shot shows a search example using the Filter row:</p>
        <p>
            <img src="../Resources/Images/Web Registration images/Filter example.gif" />
        </p>
        <p><b style="text-decoration: underline;">Related Topics:</b>
            <br /><a href="Searching the Temporary Registry.htm">Searching the Temporary Registry</a>
            <br /><a href="Searching the Registration Records.htm">Searching the Registration Records</a>
        </p>
